data.summary: [PR Newswire] - DENVER and NEW YORK, Jan. 31, 2017 /PRNewswire/ -- Farmland Partners Inc. ("FPI") (FPI) and American Farmland Company ("AFCO") (NYSE MKT: AFCO) announced that the stockholders of both companies have approved the proposed merger between FPI and AFCO. The merger is expected to close on February 2, 2017 at which time FPI will acquire all of the outstanding common stock of AFCO in a stock-for-stock transaction. Shares of the combined company's common stock will continue to trade under FPI's existing ticker symbol "FPI" on the New York Stock Exchange.

data.summary: [PR Newswire] - DENVER, and NEW YORK, Sept. 12, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- Farmland Partners Inc. (FPI) ("FPI") and American Farmland Company (NYSE MKT: AFCO) ("AFCO") jointly announced today that they have entered into a definitive agreement (the "Agreement") pursuant to which FPI has agreed to acquire all of the outstanding common stock of AFCO in a stock-for-stock transaction. The combined company will be the largest public farmland REIT in the nation spanning more than 133,000 acres across 16 states, along both Coasts, the Midwest, the Plains and the Delta. FPI's assets are comprised primarily of premier row crop farmland, while AFCO's portfolio is concentrated in high-quality specialty and permanent crop farms across the U.S. On a consolidated basis, the combined company's portfolio is expected to consist of approximately 75% row crop farmland and 25% specialty crops by value.
data.title: Farmland Partners Announces Transformative, Accretive Merger With American Farmland Company
